Sundowns were in Caf Champions League action against Botswana outfit Jwaneng Galaxy as they looked to book their spot in the group stages of the competition. They thumped their opponents 3-1 (5-1 on aggregate) in the second leg of the first-round clash played at Loftus Versfeld Stadium and marched on to the business end of the competition. Kermit Erasmus, Mothobi Mvala and Thapelo Morena were on the scoresheet for the 2016 champions. It was a good day for South African teams as Kaizer Chiefs also booked their spot in the group stages of the Champions League for the first time after they beat Angolan outfit Primeiro De Agosto 1-0 at the Est√°dio 11 de Novembro in Luanda. Leonardo Castro scored the only goal of the game while Samir Nurkovic made his long-awaited return from injury.